<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,932]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Comments. Hallowell had 
<specimenCount box="[513,683,295,319]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at hands, one from 
<collectingCountry box="[929,1067,296,320]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
, collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, and one previously deposited in the collection of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia. Hallowell clearly stated that the description was made only from the ANSP specimen, stated to be in much better condition, and, indeed only the characters of a single specimen were given by Hallowell. As a consequence, the original type locality was “Canton River”, now Zhu Jiang River, 
<collectingRegion box="[1088,1329,439,463]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Guangdong Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">People’s Republic of China</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[428,526,476,500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
was presumably ANSP 6616; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" box="[925,1111,476,500]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
Zug 
<emphasis box="[979,1036,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; lost according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
Zug 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
and N. Gilmore (pers. comm., 
<date box="[576,745,511,535]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2009-02">February 2009</date>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,932]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
In contrast to 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" box="[354,544,548,572]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
<collectingRegion box="[354,399,548,572]" country="Switzerland" name="Zug" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Zug</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[406,456,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
and in agreement with Article 73.1.2 of the 
<emphasis box="[1043,1102,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Code</emphasis>
, we consider that the original description was based on a 
<typeStatus box="[470,568,583,607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
and not on 
<specimenCount box="[710,862,584,608]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
. As a consequence, the designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[1333,1435,583,607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lectotype</typeStatus>
made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" box="[256,450,620,644]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
<collectingRegion box="[256,301,620,644]" country="Switzerland" name="Zug" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Zug</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[310,360,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
is invalid according to the 
<emphasis box="[763,822,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Code</emphasis>
(Article 74.2). In fact, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" box="[1090,1283,620,644]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
<collectingRegion box="[1090,1135,620,644]" country="Switzerland" name="Zug" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Zug</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[1142,1193,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
involuntarily designated a 
<typeStatus box="[296,387,656,680]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">neotype</typeStatus>
, based on the fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[682,780,655,679]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
is lost. The problem is that their “potential” designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[173,261,692,716]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">neotype</typeStatus>
is also invalid, as it does not comply with dispositions of Article 75 of the 
<emphasis box="[1150,1209,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Code</emphasis>
. In agreement with Article 75.3 of the 
<emphasis box="[372,431,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Code</emphasis>
, we select as 
<typeStatus box="[595,683,728,752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">neotype</typeStatus>
the specimen USNM 7387, previously designated as 
<typeStatus box="[1302,1405,727,751]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lectotype</typeStatus>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zug, G. R. &amp; Blackburn, J. L. &amp; Sai Wunna Kyi" box="[151,367,764,788]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref34170" refString="Zug, G. R., Blackburn, J. L. and Sai Wunna Kyi (2006) Checkered Keelbacks (Xenochrophis - Reptilia: Serpentes: Natricidae) at the Moyingyi Wetland Bird Sanctuary, Myanmar. Hamadryad, 30 (1 / 2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="2006">
<collectingRegion box="[151,196,764,788]" country="Switzerland" name="Zug" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Zug</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[211,268,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
. This action is justified by (1) the need to fix the nomenclatural status of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hallowell, 1861" authorityName="Hallowell" authorityYear="1861" class="Reptilia" family="Natricidae" genus="Amphiesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavipunctatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Amphiesma flavipunctatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hallowell, E." box="[326,508,799,823]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="480 - 510" refId="ref31566" refString="Hallowell, E. (1861) Report upon the Reptilia of the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, under command of Capt. John Rogers, U. S. N. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 1860, 480 - 510." type="journal article" year="1861">Hallowell, 1861</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, (2) the destruction of the 
<typeStatus box="[805,906,799,823]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
, and (3) the proximity between the localities of the 
<typeStatus box="[192,290,836,860]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
and of the 
<typeStatus box="[416,508,836,860]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
